body.description: For drivers who love new adventures while traveling, the refurbished Garmin DriveSmart 65 GPS Navigator with Bluetooth and WiFi is the ultimate road trip companion. Featuring simple menus and easy-to-read maps, Garmin DriveSmart 65 lets you view turn-by-turn directions at a glance on its bright 6.95 in. edge to edge touchscreen display. Outsmart traffic jams or slowdowns by avoiding them altogether with timely traffic alerts that suggest alternate routes to help you steer clear of construction zones or accidents ahead. Voice-activated navigation lets you say "OK Garmin" to control the device with your voice! Garmin Traffic comes ready to use right out of the box, thanks to the included traffic cable—no need to pair your navigator with a smartphone for traffic information. Traffic and map updates are included along with helpful driver alerts to encourage safer driving! Be road trip-ready with a big, bright 6.95” display and easy-to-see maps Talk to me. Enjoy the convenient voice assistant and hands-free calling. Discover where history happened with the included HISTORY database of notable sites. Plan your fun with TripAdvisor traveler ratings and a U.S. national parks directory. No computer? No problem. Built-in Wi-Fi technology wirelessly updates maps and software. Make all the right moves with clear, detailed map updates of North America.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars GOOD FOR USA BUT EU MAPS NOT ACCURATE
reviews.reviewText: The product looks and works like new so far. Bought an extra map for Europe, extra $99, but it does not work well in Eastern Europe. Some real addresses could not be found, and spelling could be sometimes problematic, frustrating. Google does it all, which means the problem is with Garmin's maps. Not real world GPS, more like regionally oriented.

Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It's got to be a Garmin GPS.
reviews.reviewText: We have a winter home North of Tampa Florida and love going to concerts. In the past I usedthe Garmin in my Nissin for travel but this year we took a plane and needed a GPS for a car wepurchased here. Through Amazon purchased an off-brand, and it directed me to turn right,not where or when. My wife got out her phone and with that she got us to our destination andhome. I returned the off-brand and purchased a Garmin DRIVESMART that works like the GarminGPS in my car at home and in my F250 pulling our 5th. wheel camperGarmin gives me timely and accurate information I need in advance, be it traffic lights, stop Signs ormy next destination for another concert in Tampa Florida. I hope this information will help othershoppers looking for a reliable (Garmin) GPS.
